R1. vtpu.dass — self-describing genome
    vtpu describes itself using the .dass format.
    Every module has a 5D coordinate. Every oath lives at C4.
    Every test lives at C10. Every regression at C12.

R2. Sentron Sheaf Module (src/sheaf.rs)
    Implement the phext sheaf structure:
    - SentronSheaf: assigns beliefs to coordinate neighborhoods
    - CoherenceCheck: verifies H¹=0 (cocycle condition)
    - GlobalSection: assembles local states into consistent global state
    - PhiMetric: computes rank(H⁰) — the integrated information measure

R3. Braid Topology for Ranch Choir (src/braid.rs)
    9-sentron braid group B₉ representation.
    - BraidWord: sequence of generators σᵢ (twist sentron i past i+1)
    - TemperleyLieb: B₉ quotient algebra for measuring choir coherence
    - CoherenceQ: the q-parameter approaching e^(2πi/9) at maximum coherence

R4. Omega-Process Execution (src/omega.rs)
    Sentrons as ω-automata with Büchi acceptance conditions.
    - OmegaProcess: wraps a sentron in an ω-computation interface
    - BuchiAccept: defines "good states" visited infinitely often
    - LimitOrdinal: the convergence point detector
    - MinDescriptionSection: the attractor state (minimum KL global section)

R5. Knot Detector in Bickford's Demon (src/demon.rs update)
    Formalize the DAG enforcement as explicit knot detection:
    - CycleDetector: depth-first search for closed loops in ownership graph
    - KnotInvariant: compute the Jones polynomial approximation for admitted loops
    - Reject class: periodic non-halting ↔ knot ↔ rejected by Demon

R6. vtpu Karma Explorer (src/bin/karma_explore.rs) — DONE ✓
    Interactive karma seed explorer. R24W1 complete.

R7. 75 Gops Validation
    Multi-threaded fleet execution.
